      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate the full range of clinically relevant loading configurations, including at minimum two angulation offsets and two construct lengths, with environmental controls documented per ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single standardized ASTM F1717 configuration (45-degree offset, standard block spacing) across two laboratories. Although inter-laboratory reproducibility was demonstrated, only one mechanical test condition was evaluated. The required Gradation 3 demands at minimum two distinct loading configurations to bound model predictions across the COU envelope; only Gradation 2 was achieved. This gap is noted but the overall assessment is declared High assurance based on strong output comparison metrics.",
