    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team reviewed all 13 V&V 40 credibility factors. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The Test conditions factor achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 due to single-configuration testing; however, the team judged that inter-laboratory reproducibility across N=11 specimens and strong quantitative output comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96) provide sufficient confidence to accept the model for the stated COU. Overall assurance level is declared High based on the preponderance of satisfactory factor assessments and passing quantitative acceptance criteria.",
